cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on open set domain adaptation (OSDA), which involves dealing with unknown classes, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, indicating a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method involves training two networks to mutually supervise each other, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
